{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about","content_id":"38fbfc5e-2094-4fa2-948a-fdcfd80233b5","description":"We’re a group commissioned by the Prime Minister to provide advice on how best to create a permanent and fitting tribute to the Windrush generation and their descendants. ","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>The permanent members of the committee are all influential voices within the UK’s Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic (BAME) communities and many of us have a direct personal connection to the Windrush generation.</p>\n\n<p>The committee is supported by a secretariat from the Department for Levelling Up, Housing and Communities.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"permanent-members\">Permanent members</h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>Baroness Floella Benjamin, Chair, Liberal Democrat peer and former broadcaster and television presenter</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Paulette Simpson, Deputy Chair, executive director of The Voice, Britain’s leading black newspaper</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Rev Rose Hudson-Wilkin, Chaplain to the speaker of the House of Commons</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Tim Campbell MBE, entrepreneur and winner of the first series of BBC’s The Apprentice</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Geoff Thompson MBE, educationist and founder of the Youth Charter</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Sir Ken Olisa, businessman and philanthropist and current Lord Lieutenant of Greater London</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Ansel Wong, cultural activist, former chair of the Notting Hill Carnival board</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>George ‘George the Poet’ Mpanga, spoken word artist and social commentator</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Simon Frederick, artist, photographer and filmmaker. Well known for documentaries and exhibitions such as Black is the New Black</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-06-21T16:48:17Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[{"contents":["bbff6f31-5820-468e-835d-56ef58b12d4b"],"name":"Access our information"}],"headers":[{"id":"who-we-are","level":2,"text":"Who we are"},{"id":"permanent-members","level":2,"text":"Permanent members"}],"organisation":"5ee63249-c7a9-406a-b3e0-bcdc7e21437d","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"about","first_published_at":"2019-06-21T17:48:18+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about","base_path":"/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about","content_id":"38fbfc5e-2094-4fa2-948a-fdcfd80233b5","document_type":"about","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-06-21T16:48:17Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"About us","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about","withdrawn":false}],"corporate_information_pages":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about/membership","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about/membership","base_path":"/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about/membership","content_id":"bbff6f31-5820-468e-835d-56ef58b12d4b","document_type":"membership","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2019-06-21T08:58:27Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"Membership","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee/about/membership","withdrawn":false}],"organisations":[{"analytics_identifier":"OT1285","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/windrush-commemoration-committee","base_path":"/government/organisation